Class: aQuery

aQuery

new aQuery(elem, tagName, parent)

You can config global name. See AMDQuery.html
aQuery("div") equivalent to new aQuery("div").
Parameters:
Name Type Argument Default Description
elem Object | String | Element | Array.<Element> | function
tagName String <optional>
 "div" Tag name if a is a object.
parent Element <optional>
 Parent Element.
Source:
  • amdquery.js, line 262
Example
aQuery(function(){}); // Equivalent to ready(function(){}), see module:base/ready
// should require("main/query")
aQuery("div"); aQuery("#my"); aQuery(".title") // see http://sizzlejs.com/
aQuery(div); aQuery([div, div]);
aQuery(aQuery("div")); // another aQuery
// should require("main/css")
aQuery({height:100,width:100},"div"); // create a element "div", style is "height:100px;width:100px"
aQuery(null,"a"); // create a element "a" without style
// should require("main/dom")
aQuery({height:100,width:100},"div", document.body); // create a element "div" and append to "body"
aQuery(null,"div", document.body);
